Subject: [PATCH] remove the release timer from all pcmcia net drivers
Message-ID: <20030724085839.GA9748@lst.de>
Mail-Followup-To: Christoph Hellwig <hch>, jgarzik@pobox.com,
	linux-pcmcia@lists.infradead.org, linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
Mime-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii
Content-Disposition: inline
User-Agent: Mutt/1.3.28i
X-Spam-Score: -3 () PATCH_UNIFIED_DIFF,USER_AGENT_MUTT
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org

The release timer in the pcmcia drivers is not needed at all and
only causes potential problems when the functions called from
it aren't safe for timer context.  This patch kills it in all
pcmcia network driver similar to the 2.4 scsi patch I just forward
ported to 2.5.  Other pcmcia drivers will follow soon.


